Eddie Mars is the novel's antagonist, the thoroughly corrupt leader of a gambling racket who has at least an indirect hand in almost all the murders that take place in the novel. Though Mars is a ruthless man, he will not taint his own hands with blood; instead, he hires others to do his dirty work. He manages a hold on many of the characters in the book through his manipulative threats and offered "protection."Read anin-depth analysis of Eddie Mars.